snippet.title: U.N. Squadron (SNES) Full Run on Gamer Difficulty
snippet.description:
U.N. Squadron (エリア88) aka Area 88
System & Settings: Super Nintendo (SNES), "Gamer" difficulty mode (hardest)

Stage Listing:
0:00 Start
0:16 Mission 1 - Front Line Base
2:03 Mission 2 - Enemy Air Force
7:12 Mission 3 - Desert Ground Carrier
12:01 Mission 4 - Forrest Fortress
15:42 Mission 5 - Wolfpack Squadron
18:42 Mission 6 - Submarine Seavet
21:56 Mission 7 - Battleship Minks
25:04 Mission 8 - Canyon
29:04 Mission 9 - Mountain Cavern
32:47 Mission 10 - Project 4 Fortress
38:48 - Ending + Credits

This video shows a full run of UN Squadron for the SNES on the special "Gamer" difficulty mode, playing on real SNES hardware.

Gamer difficulty is selected by going to options, holding down X and A on controller 2, and then pushing right on the d-pad twice on controller 1.

This game is pretty brutal on "Gamer" difficulty, and I die numerous times early on.  Near the end it comes down to my last life and even my very last hit.
